<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="408" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24354/4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Monroe</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                    Jose</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-05"><hi rend="italic">May 5,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Monroe reports destruction of Cartago by earthquake, during which it
                            is estimated that 500 persons were killed or wounded. Says court of
                            peace was destroyed. Reports that Americans are safe. Adds that San Jose
                            was badly shaken, but says no lives were lost.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>